Casper is a Composer and Educational Anthropologist. In January 2019 he was on a vacation in Cali, Colombia. Random circumstances gave him the opportunity to do a â€˜1-day ethnographyâ€™ in SiloÃ©. SiloÃ© is a neighborhood with a long history and a lot of culture. It is also considered â€œCaliâ€™s most dangerous barrio (neighbourhood)â€œ. The occasion was a project, â€˜Los Tambores de SiloÃ©â€™ - an open air music class, where children from the barrio learned how to play on homemade instruments made from recycled materials.
During our festival, Casper will introduce you to the â€˜piece of lived lifeâ€™, via some footage from the project. This will also be an occasion to invite the participants to experiment with what we perceive when we (think we) perceive the same thing - a question central to ethnography, as well as our everyday lives.  #casperhernandezcordes #cali #colombia #lostamboresdesiloÃ© #visualanthropology #ethnomusicology #anthropology #sjÃ³nanthrofilmfest #sjÃ³n #copenhagen #kÃ¸benhavn #verdenskulturcentret #aula #nÃ¸rrebro #ibyen #mitkbh #brugbyen #filmfestival#ramenğŸœ is perfect for february in #copenhagen @ramentobiirunbro #nÃ¸rrebroOn the second day of SjÃ³n Anthro Film Fest, we have a full day planned, filled with workshops, anthropological films and interactive performances ğŸ”¥
One such film is the collaborative documentary project Dizhsa Nabani made by Sabea K. Evans, Kathryn Goldberg, Marcelo Jauregui-Volpe, Edward Ogborn, Catherine Rodgers, and MoisÃ©s GarcÃ­a GuzmÃ¡n, which explores the relationship between identity, language, and daily life in the Valley Zapotec community of San JerÃ³nimo Tlacochahuaya.
Zapotec languages are considered threatened as they are being acquired as native languages by fewer and fewer people. Community and individual identity are entwined with language, especially in Mexico, where criteria for self-identifying as belonging to an indigenous community usually includes speaking the corresponding language. Most Zapotec people today are bilingual, and under pressure from anti-indigenous discrimination, many choose to use Spanish in contexts that were previously reserved as Zapotec-language domains, including the home, the market, and town meetings. Given this sociolinguistic context, speaking Zapotec can be seen as an act of resistance.
â°Saturday, March 9th, 13:30 // Free entry ğŸ‘ˆğŸ¼ #dizhsanabani #zapotec #sanjeronimotlacochahuaya #mexico #antropologia #visualanthropology #ethnomusicology #anthropology #sjÃ³nanthrofilmfest #sjÃ³n #copenhagen #kÃ¸benhavn #verdenskulturcentret #aula #nÃ¸rrebro #ibyen #mitkbh #brugbyen #filmfestival#superkilen #kÃ¸benhavn #nÃ¸rrebro #denmark#CopenhagenğŸ’—#nightlive#nightscroll #eatingout#brus#nÃ¸rrebro#friendship#celebrating#Pemba is a Himalayan Sherpa, the Nepalese ethnic group famous worldwide for giving support to western mountaineers on the highest peaks in the world. However, Pemba has never climbed a mountain; she is a folk singer who fled her country years ago due to the civil war in the 1990s, and that now has a new life with her family in Catalonia, Spain.
Twenty years later, Pemba decides to return to her hometown, Goli, a tiny village located on a secluded plateau in the heart of the Himalayas and totally isolated from progress, to organize a concert and discover what remains of the paradise where she grew up.
Join us for Pembaâ€™s heart warming journey as followed by director Josep Perez, and discover what life is like in one of the most mythical places on Earth.

Info: 
The new album consists entirely of original compositions that mix the gypsy style with inspiration from modern jazz and Balkan. The band is clearly very well acquainted with the traditional gypsy jazz style, and the line-up is classic with guitars, violin and bass. However, the band seeks to challenge the genre and explore new directions in terms of harmonies, melodies and influences from other genres. This exploration takes the listener through lightning fast pieces, crooked melodies, beautiful ballads and to the kind of vibe that reminds you of an old gangster movie. #jazz #gypsyjazz #cph #cphbeer #nÃ¸rrebrobryghus #nÃ¸rrebro #nÃ¸rrebrogade #ryesgade #ravnsborggade @noerrebrobryghusForÃ¥ret nÃ¦rmer sig, sÃ¥ mÃ¥ det vÃ¦re pÃ¥ tide med lidt kortere forÃ¥rshÃ¥r ğŸŒ±Lang skarp page af Top Trainee @karinkristinad fra ZENZ Guldbergsgade #zenzorganic #zenzorganichairdressing #hairdresser #hair #longbob #organicbeauty #frisÃ¸r #frisÃ¸rkÃ¸benhavn #kÃ¸benhavn #nÃ¸rrebro #Ã¸sterbro #frederiksberg #lyngbyOh La LağŸ’¥

This film presents an African talking drums version of Georg Friedrich HÃ¤ndel's Hallelujah chorus, as staged and performed by legendary drummer Ghanaba together with the Winneba Youth Choir. Ghanaba's unique approach to HÃ¤ndel mixes elements of African, Christian, and Islamic ritual with formal European concert performance, Ghanaian ceremony, and improvisation.
All are welcome, and the admission to the screenings is free of charge. Looking forward to hosting you!

#Ã¥shildthorsen #tibetansingingbowl #visualanthropology #ethnomusicology #anthropology #sjÃ³nanthrofilmfest #sjÃ³n #copenhagen #kÃ¸benhavn #verdenskulturcentret #aula #nÃ¸rrebro #ibyen #mitkbh #brugbyen #filmfestivalOn Friday the 8th of March Chilean music engineer, Tania Oyarzo, will do a workshop about audio post production. 
The workshop is directed to anyone interested in learning about the production and editing of audio. 
Audio post production is the general term for all stages of audio production relating to sound produced and synchronized with moving picture (film, television or video). This includes, but is often distinguished from Production Audio, which is the audio recorded as filming/shooting occurs.

D.N.T. Diebenkorn NordicTranslations 
Number 14. Gouache on Paper.

This series is inspired by working in the studio by invitation of Marty McCutcheon at 2571 Shattuck Avenue, Berkeley, California. An historical building with a strong attachment to Californian painting as the building had in its time provided studio space for the renowned Bay Area painters David Parks, Elmer Bischoff and Richard Diebenkorn.

#Tilsalg #SÃ¦lges #StineGoya #DesignersRemix #HÃ¥rbÃ¸jle #HÃ¥rbÃ¸jler #HÃ¥rpynt #kÃ¸benhavn #NÃ¸rrebro #Genbrugsmaterialer #Recycle #Recycled #Genbrugsguld #Danishdesign #Denmark #Danmark #Forsale #guld #Genbrug  #Diadem #Diademer #Hairband #Ganni #Danishdesign #Blogger #KÃ¸benhavn #Scandinaviandesign #BÃ¦redygtigt #BÃ¦redygtigtDesignBLAA GALLERI is pleased to announce ON THE OTHER SIDE - a solo exhibition by Christian Gundtoft 9/3 â€“ 5/4 2019

Opening on the 9th of March 2019 at 5:00 PM

Last time Christian Gundtoft had a solo exhibition here at BLAA, in 2018, it was called ON THE BRINK. This time around he finds himself on the other side, on the other side of what he was on the brink to - it can be understood as a reference to his artistic process. Constantly experimenting and evolving, always on the lookout for that one source of inspiration that never seizes up. He has as of late been working tirelessly on an amalgamation of his various styles and modes of expression in his painting, and the result is this exhibition. 
The exhibition title can also be understood as a reference to the motives in the artworks themselves. Christian purposefully wants them to be ambiguous as to what the motive really is, and offers a plethora of alternative interpretations, each one as valid, strong and believable as the other.

Rest assured, Christianâ€™s paintings are as surrealistic and expressive as ever, gritty and explosive, bristling with detail. The compositions are akin to an expanding chaos, yet upon close scrutiny recognizable shapes and familiar objects become crystalized and take over the narrative of the painting which opens for widely different interpretations.

For this exhibition we will present Christian Gundtoftâ€™s most recent works, presented to the public for the very first time. On the opening night, we will also have a musical contribution from Linebug, an audio/visual collaboration between songwriter Line BÃ¸gh and Christian Gundtoft himself.

Number 11. Gouache on Paper.

This series is inspired by working in the studio by invitation of Marty McCutcheon at 2571 Shattuck Avenue, Berkeley, California. I started playing this instrument when I was 12 years old and before I knew it I was put into a brass band. 
The other musicians where mostly old guys drinking coffee and smoking cigars during  breaks. 
Being a kid I found them and the brass genre pretty boring, so me and my three best friends quickly made our own jazz quartet and played the streets all summer with a hat for tips. It turned out to be a pretty good business and after a day of busking we would always go to the nearest cafÃ¨ and use our earnings on hot chocolat ğŸ˜‡

Sofie is currently in her gap year and is in the process of applying for an education within veterinarian medicine. She chooses this path because she loves animals and would like to help them in her own way. 
During the time she is not here at @cafemellemrummet , she is a substitute teacher for primary students at her previous school. She says she loves teaching and most of all interacting with the kids in her class. 
She also does not stop there, as she keeps up some hobbies in her free time. She does archery, loves to read and does bungee jumping. She is also very brave, as the highest jump she has ever had was from around 300m tall. How many of us could say we could do it ğŸ˜„?
It is also no surprise that she is currently with us, as her father used to work for @mellemfolkeligtsamvirke . When she was younger, she visited Africa with her dad for a work related trip. We are sure her father is proud of where she is and most importantly, what she does ğŸ™‚
Please donâ€™t hesitate to say hi to her if youâ€™re here and we wish her the best in the near future

#femalepreneur #womeninbiz #startyourownbusiness #dreamersandoers #entrepreneurwoman #workshopspace #mitkÃ¸benhavn #nÃ¸rrebro #vÃ¦rksted#CafeAuto #NÃ¸rrebro #Coffee #CoffeeAndRum #Rum #Zacapa #AfterDinnerCoffee #GoodFriendDinner #Copenhagen #DenmarkThis Beautiful Photo was taken in Copenhagen, Denmark. Amazing place where I spent many years of by young teenage wild life. It became my second home.  I lived up the road close to a nightclub called Nightglass where we used to party all night until early morning. I was so young. Those were the days. In the immigrant area called Norrebro. taking Bus 5 a daily. For free. Eating Danish pastry. Going to flea markets. I was young, naive and beautiful. Totally unaware. Those were the days.  They used to have a market every Saturday where they sold used beautiful things. Being in Norrebro is like being outside of Europe. Totally wild.  A lot has changed the last 15 years. Copenhagen changes daily. I used to work in the Caribbean cafe for a short time with the insane owner and his Polish rude girlfriend. I wasted years of my life being in the toxic relation with the much older male who came to Denmark as a young guy married to an older Danish woman.  I do not longer travel to Denmark often. I canâ€™t afford it. Itâ€™s crazy expensive unless one is rich.  We used to party in the apartment on top of fotex. We used to party in Vega and Christiania. Loppen. Rust. Hiphop. Reggae. Dancehall. It was a different life. Copenhagen felt like New York. Now I am old and I hardly leave my home. I miss being wild and young and careless.  I feel like a 98 year old grandmother now.  All was much more fun 15-20 years ago in life.  Much more exciting. All countries were much more fun back in the days. Life was better back in the days. Now life is dry and boring.  Now we can live on the memories and photos we took many years ago. People used to meet and play football and make barbecue in the park. There was much social unity. Now they are building a metro in the immigrant area. Feels like you are on Somalia or Iraq when you walk there. Copenhagen has many nice places. Segregated. The Danish currency is strong. They earn great money there. Diebenkorn NordicTranslations 
Number 24. Gouache on Paper.

This series is inspired by working in the studio by invitation of Marty McCutcheon at 2571 Shattuck Avenue, Berkeley, California. An historical building with a strong attachment to Californian painting as the building had in its time provided studio space for the renowned Bay Area painters David Parks, Elmer Bischoff and Richard Diebenkorn.

Henry the Rabbit on his influences and inspirations: â€œFloods, apocalyptic texts and visions, nature, life and death, goats, mythology, flying things, eschatological and apocryphal texts, ecstatic visionaries, high spirited rosy cheeked creatures of the flesh, tarot, Japanese landscapes; those are the things of inspiration. I enjoy contemplating the past and continue to commune with the dead. Sometimes the living ones make me uneasy: I appreciate cave painters, the Egyptians, the Babylonians, the Medievalists as much as 16th century court painters. I love the ghosts of the German expressionists and the Japanese woodblock printers. I talk to Vincent Van Gogh despite Jehovah's advice of 'do not consult the dead on behalf of the livingâ€™. If I could choose to take inspiration from anywhere, it would come from Outsiders; those who create without reward and have no thought for it. Driven by passion and the unseen forces that determine them. These I find more inspiring than todayâ€™s self willed, self conscious, self branding and promoting - instagram / art fair artists or the academy careerists. Occultists, mystics, mythologists, natural philosophers, adventurers, folks who live by their own rules, are not these the people who inspire art?

#hamabeads #hamaperler #perlerbeads #bÃ¼gelperlen #perleplader #beadart #beadstreetart #gadekunstikÃ¸benhavn #gadekunst #streetart #streetartcopenhagen #streetartcph #streetarteverywhere #streetartisnotdead #pixelart #meltybeads #ironbeads #fusebeads #voreskbh #sharingcph #delditkbh #ibyen #nÃ¸rrebro #wearenÃ¸rrebroFits like a glove #likeaglove #seenoutandabout #hands #poster #gaffatapewillholdupanything #morninglaugh #copenhagen #nÃ¸rrebro #wallWe stumbled across Assistens Cemetery in Copenhagen on an early morning walk.
Unlike most cemeteries I have visited which have one function, Assistens is also a park and NÃ¸rrebro's largest greenspace. Visitors are encouraged to use the non-burial parts of the cemetery for recreational purposes (ie. Jogging, dog walking, picnics, sunbathing, socialising and having a good time), as long as they are respectful to the funerals being held and people visiting their loved ones graves. I think this is a lovely idea! Walking through the cemetery was peaceful despite people going about their exercise or relaxation activities. It was quiet... but the vibrancy of life being lived and nature blooming brought happiness to what could otherwise be seen as a gloomy place. Life really does go on after death and this park epitomises the juxtaposition of the two states of being (or not being)... and shows that they coexist in harmony, as you can not have one without the other. It has been said the value of life is determined by death, so what better place to celebrate life, (both past and present) and the joy of living ğŸ’• #assistenskirkegÃ¥rd #cemetery #greenspace #nÃ¸rrebro #copenhagen #europetrip #scandinavianlife

Number 9. Gouache on Paper.

This series is inspired by working in the studio by invitation of Marty McCutcheon at 2571 Shattuck Avenue, Berkeley, California. An historical building with a strong attachment to Californian painting as the building had in its time provided studio space for the renowned Bay Area painters David Parks, Elmer Bischoff and Richard Diebenkorn.

#Tilsalg #SÃ¦lges #StineGoya #DesignersRemix #HÃ¥rbÃ¸jle #HÃ¥rbÃ¸jler #HÃ¥rpynt #kÃ¸benhavn #NÃ¸rrebro #Genbrugsmaterialer #Recycle #Recycled #Genbrugsguld #Danishdesign #Denmark #Danmark #Forsale #guld #Genbrug  #Diadem #Diademer #Hairband #Smykker #Smykke #Ã¸rering #Ã¸reringe #earring #earringsSuper fedt verdenskort k kÃ¸benhavnervenlig stÃ¸rrelse 162x118. Har en lille skade i stangen forneden. Deraf prisen 1600,- #verdenskort #skolekort #loppefund #loppeguld #loppemarked #nÃ¸rrebro #delditkbh #tilsalg #sÃ¦lges #loppesalg #genbrugsguld #genbrugssalg #retrosalg #retroguld #retro#patented #bottletops found the other day with @cphimport - Both of the probably from the #1930s. The green top is from a small #brewery, that used to be located in #baldersgade in the #borrow of #NÃ¸rrebro in #Copenhagen. To my knowledge it closed down in the #1970s. The red #Carlsberg top is interesting because it features the #swastika that was adobted by the #NSDAP as their 
#symbol. Before it became a #nazi symbol it was regarded as the symbol of life and good #fortune in several #cultures. The #founder of Carlsberg I C Jacobsen chose the 12-pointed #star as logo for his lable, while his son Carl Jacobsen later made the #swastika as the logo for Ny Carlsberg. Often the swastika in his logo was seen with four dots within the arms. After year 1906 the swastika and the 12-pointed star was often seen combined as seen in this top. In #1940 when Denmark was uccupied by #germany as part of #ww2, Carlsberg stopped using this symbol. Today you actually still see the symbol #engraved in the huges stone #elephants placed by the gates of the old Carlsberg site in Copenhagen. #metaldetecting #dailyfinds #detectingfinds #garrettatpro #atpro #digginghistoryDet her er god stil, synes vi!ğŸ‘ğŸ»ğŸ‘ğŸ»ğŸ‘ğŸ»

This series is inspired by working in the studio by invitation of Marty McCutcheon at 2571 Shattuck Avenue, Berkeley, California. Pavlos On The Beach
Courtesy Hans Manner Jakobsen

The image is of my favourite young man. My dear son Pavlos making his photographic contribution while we are scouting locations on the North Coast of Denmark. Pavlos is a T.N.G. The Next Generation. The generation that we are pinning all our hopes upon to salvage the catastrophic global mess that subsequent generations (including mine) by lack of humane reasoning, wanton greed, and an absence of social empathy have created, almost to the point of no return.
